The faint clink of metal drifted down the passageway, and Cody froze mid-step. “The shopkeeper again, no doubt,” he said to himself, and smiled as he heard someone counting in the distance. “An odd place for a shop,” he added, “but he wouldn't be here if there wasn't a market.” The image of a queue of jackals, all patiently waiting with grocery baskets, came to mind.
